# Minified widget JS: COMMITTED since v2.9.5 (was gitignored). A plain
# `jmc --build` on a fresh clone must produce a working module - without
# min.js the runtime falls back to inlining the ~6 MB source, which can
# freeze the results webview (the v2.4.1 regression; re-hit by a
# jamovi-team from-source build, Jul 2026). The Stop hook + release.sh
# + CI keep it fresh; R/widget.R's hash check refuses a stale copy.

# Shipped user guide (generated from docs/ by scripts/jmv-build-install.sh
# and the CI workflow; docs/ is the canonical copy)
inst/docs/

# Local architecture/codebase diagrams (kept out of release history)
docs/diagrams/

# distribution output (jamovi team builds these; never committed)
dist/

# personal dev docs -- kept locally, not distributed publicly
/LAUNCH-QA-CHECKLIST*.html
/PLOT_STUDIO_BACKLOG.md
/docs/tab-mapping-spec.md

# dev-only: project instructions + prototypes/experiments (kept local, not public)
/CLAUDE.md
/prototypes/

# reference copies of upstream source dropped in for local study (jmv /
# jamovi app code) - NEVER commit into this repo (AGPL upstream + bloat;
# release.sh stages with `git add -A`, so this guard is load-bearing)
/Jamovi Source Files/
/Jamovi Source Code/
